    {
      "id": "5a93c517_37b8ba74",
      "file_path": "appc-provider/appc-provider-model/src/main/yang/appc-provider-lcm.yang",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "there is the same typedef ZULU at appc-provide.yang. if you only change this file, then the typedef ZULU is not getting in-sync. I don't recommend to extend more digits in here. it's a trivial change and we have to make sure for the backwards compatible to deal with the complexity of this application.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2477,
        "name": "Takamune Cho",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "takamune.cho@att.com",
        "username": "Takamune_Cho"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-19 13:17:47.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_771ac27d",
      "file_path": "appc-provider/appc-provider-model/src/main/yang/appc-provider-lcm.yang",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "Current regex causes intermittent test failures and could also cause intermittent failures in operation. It would also lead to failures nearly 100% of the time on a system that returns current time with nanosecond rather than millisecond precision. Please advise whether to also change the appc-provider.yang file to the correct regex or to abandon this change.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3979,
        "name": "Joss Armstrong",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "joss.armstrong@ericsson.com",
        "username": "jarmstrong001"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-19 14:12:45.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_37b8ba74",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_f20ca03b",
      "file_path": "appc-provider/appc-provider-model/src/main/yang/appc-provider-lcm.yang",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "We probably do not need nanosecond precision. I assume if you remove testTimestampFormatLong(), and revert the change back in yang file. the tests would go through?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2477,
        "name": "Takamune Cho",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "takamune.cho@att.com",
        "username": "Takamune_Cho"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-19 14:32:35.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_771ac27d",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_126d8ccc",
      "file_path": "appc-provider/appc-provider-model/src/main/yang/appc-provider-lcm.yang",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "The tests will work when Clock.systemUTC method returns a millisecond (or microsecond) precision time with a non-zero fractional component. With the original regex whenever the method is invoked at a time where the fractional component of the time is zero it will fail. E.G. at x seconds and zero milliseconds.\nAlso, Clock.systemUTC method uses the most accurate available clock on the system where it is running which is System.getCurrentTimeMillis() on most systems but will be a higher precision clock if one is available. This will cause nearly all invocations to fail if nanosecond precision time is returned by Clock object. https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/Clock.html#systemUTC--\nSee also related JIRA: https://jira.onap.org/browse/APPC-1009",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3979,
        "name": "Joss Armstrong",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "joss.armstrong@ericsson.com",
        "username": "jarmstrong001"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-19 14:43:18.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_f20ca03b",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_12982c69",
      "file_path": "appc-provider/appc-provider-model/src/main/yang/appc-provider-lcm.yang",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "when we built LCM response header we used DateFormat ZULU_FORMATTER = new SimpleDateFormat(\"yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SS'Z'\") on ResponseBuildHeader.class. that may link to your jenkins failed on test case.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2477,
        "name": "Takamune Cho",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "takamune.cho@att.com",
        "username": "Takamune_Cho"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-19 17:12:00.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_126d8ccc",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_7d6061a4",
      "file_path": "appc-provider/appc-provider-model/src/main/yang/appc-provider-lcm.yang",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "In the case that the CommonHeader object is instantiated using the constructor of CommonHeader class that takes an existing CommonHeader object this format is applied. \nWhen the setTimestamp method of the CommonHeader class is used to set the timestamp this check format is not applied and when the CommonHeaderBuilder is used to construct a CommonHeader implementation then the format is not applied either. The date formatting seems to be mainly done in the classes using the CommonHeader.setTimestamp and the CommonHeaderBuilder methods of instantiating these objects so I was not able to find a case that would cause failures in operation.\nThe regex pattern in ZULU does not match the DateFormat definitions defined in various classes but it is less restrictive so will not fail. I will change this code review to just apply the DateFormat to the timestamp of the CommonHeader objects instantiated within the intermittently failing tests and remove the proposed changes to this YANG definition.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3979,
        "name": "Joss Armstrong",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "joss.armstrong@ericsson.com",
        "username": "jarmstrong001"
      },
      "updated": "2018-06-20 11:58:10.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_12982c69",
      "unresolved": false
    }
